T*
() Tj
T*
(Summary) Tj
T*
(Genetics is a valuable part of Biology. Students perform better when they understand) Tj
T*
(genes, alleles, and inheritance patterns, learn from examples such as using a Punnett) Tj
T*
(square for a simple trait, and deliberately avoid mistakes like confusing genotype with) Tj
T*
(phenotype. Regular practice built around inheritance and trait prediction makes the) Tj
